HEADWORD: Wincing
<hw>Win"cing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of washing
cloth, dipping it in dye, etc., with a wince.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Wincing machine</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A wince.</cd>
<au>Ure.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>A succession of winces. See
<er>Wince</er>.</cd> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wincopipe</ent>⟦br⟧
